<subsection id="domain-spec-step-4-3">
  <title>Step 4-3. Add .ent File to Shell</title>
  <prolog>
    <author>W. Eliot Kimber</author>
    <copyright>
			<?oxy_attributes year="&lt;change type=&quot;modified&quot; oldValue=&quot;2007&quot; author=&quot;jdwin&quot; timestamp=&quot;20200109T093827-0500&quot; /&gt;"?>
			<copyryear year="2020"/>
			<copyrholder>W. Eliot Kimber</copyrholder>
		</copyright>    
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>Add the domain entity declaration (.ent) file to concept.dtd. In your copy of concept.dtd,
			find the comment that says "DOMAIN ENTITY DECLARATIONS" and following this comment add the
			following parameter entity declaration and reference:
			<codeblock>
&lt;!ENTITY % <?oxy_delete author="jdwin" timestamp="20200109T094051-0500" content="xml"?><?oxy_insert_start author="jdwin" timestamp="20200109T094053-0500"?>dbPara<?oxy_insert_end?>-d-dec     
   SYSTEM "<?oxy_delete author="jdwin" timestamp="20200109T094100-0500" content="xml"?><?oxy_insert_start author="jdwin" timestamp="20200109T094102-0500"?>dbPara<?oxy_insert_end?>Domain.ent"                                                
>
%<?oxy_delete author="jdwin" timestamp="20200109T094108-0500" content="xml"?><?oxy_insert_start author="jdwin" timestamp="20200109T094109-0500"?>dbPara<?oxy_insert_end?>-d-dec;  
</codeblock>
		</p>
    <p>The system identifier needs to reflect the actual location of the
			<?oxy_delete author="jdwin" timestamp="20200109T094137-0500" content="xml"?><?oxy_insert_start author="jdwin" timestamp="20200109T094138-0500"?>dbPara<?oxy_insert_end?>Domain.ent
			file. The example assumes that concept.dtd and
			<?oxy_delete author="jdwin" timestamp="20200109T094147-0500" content="xml"?><?oxy_insert_start author="jdwin" timestamp="20200109T094149-0500"?>dbPara<?oxy_insert_end?>Domain.ent
			are in the same directory.</p>
  </body>
</subsection>
